We were even able to deal with CLOB, the stock market set up by Singapore. 

15.I am just curious. We have more savings and reserves now compared to 1997- 8. Yet I am told that if we peg, we may go bankrupt?

label: Politician

description: Official Account | 4th & 7th Prime Minister of Malaysia | MP for Langkawi | Parti PEJUANG | e-mail: drmahathir@perdana.org.my | facebook.com/tundrmahathir |
tweets: 14. The fact remains that the pegging was successful. As mentioned above the IMF and World Bank admitted that Malaysia did the right thing and helped other countries to overcome the serious devaluation of their currencies also.
label: Politician

description: Official Account | 4th & 7th Prime Minister of Malaysia | MP for Langkawi | Parti PEJUANG | e-mail: drmahathir@perdana.org.my | facebook.com/tundrmahathir |
tweets: 13. There were problems of course. But we were able to set up subcommittees to deal with them in 1998. This included the recapitalisation of banks and businesses.
label: Politician

description: Official Account | 4th & 7th Prime Minister of Malaysia | MP for Langkawi | Parti PEJUANG | e-mail: drmahathir@perdana.org.my | facebook.com/tundrmahathir |
tweets: Now the Central Bank has more reserves in USD, I believe. Earnings in USD should be deposited with the Central Bank, in exchange for Ringgits. There should be no shortage of USD when needed.
label: Politician

description: Official Account | 4th & 7th Prime Minister of Malaysia | MP for Langkawi | Parti PEJUANG | e-mail: drmahathir@perdana.org.my | facebook.com/tundrmahathir |
tweets: 12. In 1998 the Central Bank had less reserves. We did not know whether the reserves were held in cash, and if in cash, in what currency. Still, we were able to change Ringgit into USD so as to pay in USD.
label: Politician

description: Official Account | 4th & 7th Prime Minister of Malaysia | MP for Langkawi | Parti PEJUANG | e-mail: drmahathir@perdana.org.my | facebook.com/tundrmahathir |
tweets: 11. Wherever an importer wishes to buy something in U.S. Dollar, the Central Bank should have enough USD to sell at the pegged rate i.e. RM3.80 per USD.
label: Politician

description: Official Account | 4th & 7th Prime Minister of Malaysia | MP for Langkawi | Parti PEJUANG | e-mail: drmahathir@perdana.org.my | facebook.com/tundrmahathir |
tweets: 10. Assuming that the Ringgit remains pegged at RM3.80 per USD, the cost in Ringgit would not change. Budget estimates would be sustainable.
label: Politician

description: Official Account | 4th & 7th Prime Minister of Malaysia | MP for Langkawi | Parti PEJUANG | e-mail: drmahathir@perdana.org.my | facebook.com/tundrmahathir |
tweets: Logistical cost would also increase, again reducing the gain from production cost. A depreciated Ringgit does not necessarily reduce cost of production.
label: Politician

description: Official Account | 4th & 7th Prime Minister of Malaysia | MP for Langkawi | Parti PEJUANG | e-mail: drmahathir@perdana.org.my | facebook.com/tundrmahathir |
tweets: 9. When the Ringgit depreciates the cost of production would be lower if there is no pay revision upwards. On the other hand, the cost of imported raw materials and components would increase and negate the gain from lower wages.
label: Politician

description: Official Account | 4th & 7th Prime Minister of Malaysia | MP for Langkawi | Parti PEJUANG | e-mail: drmahathir@perdana.org.my | facebook.com/tundrmahathir |
tweets: 8. On the other hand, if the Ringgit is pegged at 3.80 the cost of import would be only 3.8 million Ringgit per 1 million USD.  A pegged Ringgit would save 700,000 Ringgit in the cost of import.

description: Minister van Economische Zaken en Klimaat | Redactie door @MinisterieEZK
tweets:
We staan voor grote uitdagingen. Onze economie moet verduurzamen. In de haven van Rotterdam wordt daar samen met de overheid hard aan gewerkt.

(8/8)
label: Politician

description: Minister van Economische Zaken en Klimaat | Redactie door @MinisterieEZK
tweets:
De overheid zet daarom ook stevig in op het vergroten van het aantal technici en ICT-professionals, het verbeteren van de aansluiting van het onderwijs op de arbeidsmarkt en procesinnovatie. De Topsectoren blijven investeren in opleiding en scholing.

(7/8)
label: Politician

description: Minister van Economische Zaken en Klimaat | Redactie door @MinisterieEZK
tweets:
Daarnaast is goed opgeleid en genoeg personeel nodig om het tekort op de arbeidsmarkt terug te dringen. Bedrijven hebben last van het tekort. Er zijn op dit moment meer vacatures dan werklozen. 

(6/8)
label: Politician

description: Minister van Economische Zaken en Klimaat | Redactie door @MinisterieEZK
tweets:
De overheid zet in op meerdere middelen om de klimaatdoelen te halen en groene industrie te stimuleren, zoals de CO2-heffing, subsidies en maatwerkafspraken. In de Miljoenennota is 3 miljard euro extra beschikbaar gemaakt voor maatwerkafspraken.

(5/8)
label: Politician

description: Minister van Economische Zaken en Klimaat | Redactie door @MinisterieEZK
tweets:
We moeten alle denkkracht en creativiteit gebruiken om aan veranderingen te werken. Dat kan alleen als de overheid en het bedrijfsleven samen optrekken.

(4/8)
label: Politician

description: Minister van Economische Zaken en Klimaat | Redactie door @MinisterieEZK
tweets:

(3/8)
label: Politician

description: Minister van Economische Zaken en Klimaat | Redactie door @MinisterieEZK
tweets:
